# Node.js Microservices App

This is a simple Node.js microservices application with two services:
- `user-service`
- `product-service`

Each service is independently dockerized and deployed to AWS EKS using Kubernetes.

## ðŸ›  Deployment Steps

1. Build Docker images:
   ```bash
   docker build -t your-dockerhub/user-service:latest ./user-service
   docker build -t your-dockerhub/product-service:latest ./product-service
   docker push your-dockerhub/user-service:latest
   docker push your-dockerhub/product-service:latest
2. Deploy to EKS:
   kubectl apply -f k8s/namespace.yaml
   kubectl apply -f k8s/user-deployment.yaml
   kubectl apply -f k8s/product-deployment.yaml
   
4. Verify:
   kubectl get all -n microservices-app
   
Endpoints :

user-service: /api/users
product-service: /api/products

   
